The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 8: The Reserve Bank today allowed mutual funds to invest in foreign exchange traded funds and ADRs/GDRs of companies overseas. The fund houses can also invest in unlisted overseas securities, the RBI notification said. The apex bank also said only fully convertible debt instruments would be permitted under the FDI policy. 

 Mumbai, June 8: Shareholders of Mahindra amp; Mahindra have approved the companys plans to raise up to Rs 1,350 crore for product launch, capacity expansion and acquisitions. 

 Mumbai, June 8: idbi plans to raise $1.5 billion through currency bonds in euro in tranches for its future expansion and acquisitions. It will be a medium-term programme. 

 New Delhi, June 8: The department of telecom has issued notices to Tata Teleservices, Bharti and Reliance asking why they should not be penalised for delay in rolling out telecom networks.

 Calcutta, June 8: The demand for CTC leaf and dust in Calcutta, Siliguri and Guwahati has improved, according to a data published by J Thomas amp; Co.




